Exercise 04: ft_is_negative
Files to deliver: ft_is_negative.c
Delivery directory: ex04/ 
Authorized functions: write
-----------------------------------
• Write a function that displays "N" or "P" depending on the sign of the integer used as a parameter. 
If n is negative, it shows "N". If n is positive or zero, it shows "P".
• The prototype of the function should be as follows:
void ft_is_negative(int n);
-----------------------------------

Prototype: 
`void`: output of the function is void, nothing. 
`int n`: input of the function is int type (integer). 

On this occasion if and else statements are used. 

If condition is true (n < 0), print `N`. 

Anything else, print `P`.
